dataTwo.title: Redux-Thunk
dataTwo.description: Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used to delay the dispatch of an action, or to dispatch only if a certain condition is met.

dataTwo.title: ESLint
dataTwo.description: ESLint is an open source JavaScript linting utility originally created by Nicholas C. Zakas in June 2013. Code linting is a type of static analysis that is frequently used to find problematic patterns or code that doesn't adhere to certain style guidelines.

dataTwo.title: Babel
dataTwo.description: Babel has support for the latest version of JavaScript through syntax transformers. These plugins allow you to use new syntax, right now without waiting for browser support.

dataTwo.title: Axios
dataTwo.description: Promise based HTTP client for the browser and node.js. With Axios, you can make XMLHttpRequests from the browser or Node with the full Promise Api.

dataTwo.title: Redux-Saga
dataTwo.description: redux-saga is a library that aims to make application side effects (i.e. asynchronous things like data fetching and impure things like accessing the browser cache) easier to manage, more efficient to execute, easy to test, and better at handling failures.

dataTwo.title: ApiSauce
dataTwo.description: Babel has support for the latest version of JavaScript through syntax transformers. These plugins allow you to use new syntax, right now without waiting for browser support.

dataTwo.title: Redux-Sauce
dataTwo.description: Provides a few tools for working with Redux-based codebases. Currently includes: createReducer - declutter reducers for readability and testing createTypes - DRY define your types object from a string createActions - builds your Action Types and Action Creators at the same time resettableReducer - allows your reducers to be reset
